\par\plain {\f0\fs36\i0 Making Changes}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i0 There are various minor changes you can make to the settings to tweak this template so that it better suits your needs, as follows:}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi0\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext \tab \bullet \tab }{\f0\fs24\b1\i0 Part subtitles:}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  If you don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t want to include the titles of your \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Part\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  folders in your compiled manuscript, go to the \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Formatting\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  pane in the Compile sheet and deselect \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Title\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  for the \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Level 1\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  folder item. Then click on \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Modify\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  and then \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Title Settings\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  and remove the colon and space at the end of the title prefix (\hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Part <$R>\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0 ).}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext \tab \bullet \tab }{\f0\fs24\b1\i0 Chapter subtitles: }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 If you don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t want to include the names of your chapter folders below the chapter numbering text in the compiled document, go to the \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Formatting\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  pane in the Compile sheet and deselect \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Title\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  for the \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Level 2+\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  folder item and the \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Level 1\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  and \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Level 2\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  text items.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext \tab \bullet \tab }{\f0\fs24\b1\i0 Page header: }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 You can edit the page header in the \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Page Settings\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  pane of the Compile sheet.}{\f0\fs24\b0  You will want to enter your name and the novel title in this field to replace the placeholder text there now.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi0\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext \tab \bullet \tab }{\f0\fs24\b1 Font:}{\f0\fs24\b0  You can use the \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Formatting\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  pane in Compile to change the font used throughout the final document by selecting the document type rows and clicking the \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Modify\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  button. This will display a sample preview of the text elements; click in the text to select it and then choose the \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 A\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  button in the format bar to change the font settings.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\fi0\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext \tab \bullet \tab }{\f0\fs24\b1\i0 Working with chapters instead of scenes:}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  By default, this project is set up so that you write each scene as a separate text document. If you don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t like to break things up quite that much and would prefer to write an entire chapter in each text document, make the following changes:}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi-490\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl1{\listtext \tab 1.\tab }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Rename the \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Scene\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  documents to use your chapter titles and move them so that they are contained directly inside the \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Part\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  folders (that is, at the same level as the current \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Chapter\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  folders).}
\par\plain \ilvl1{\listtext \tab 2.\tab }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Move the chapter folders to the Trash.}
\par\plain \ilvl1{\listtext \tab 3.\tab }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Create a new text document for each chapter.}
\par\plain \ilvl1{\listtext \tab 4.\tab }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 In the \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Separators\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  pane of the Compile sheet, change the \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Text separator\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  setting to \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 Page break\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0 .}
